	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Here's an old post, maybe you saw it. I didn't look closely. <!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://nesdev.com/bbs/viewtopic.php?p=5415#5415">http://nesdev.com/bbs/viewtopi ... =5415#5415</a><!-- m -->
<br />
<br />I can tell you that your test would find an IRQ the moment it did CLI, since the APU's frame IRQ flag would get set within a frame of powering up, and if not there, during step 4. The only way to clear it is to disable it via $4017 (set bit 6 I believe), or read $4015. And of course a dummy read of $4015 will clear it, as any read will.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


